      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For an aging Labrador, a balanced high-protein diet is key, but the ideal ratio depends on his specific activity level and health needs. Generally, look for foods with a good source of lean protein, aiming for around 25-30% protein by weight. The fat content is also important, as it provides necessary energy, but too much can lead to weight gain, so aim for a moderate fat level. Always check with your veterinarian for personalized recommendations based on your dog's overall health profile.",
