      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Splitting meals into smaller, more frequent feedings is often beneficial for senior dogs, as it can ease digestive strain and maintain more consistent energy levels. Instead of one large meal, try dividing his total daily intake into two or three smaller portions. When portioning, be careful not to overfeed, even with small meals, as too many calories can still lead to weight gain. Always follow the feeding guidelines on the food bag as a starting point, then adjust based on his body condition and activity.",
